<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Nobiin_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Consonants">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Consonants">Consonants</span></h3>
<p>Consonant length is contrastive in Nobiin, e.g. <i>dáwwí</i> 'path' vs. <i>dáwí</i> 'kitchen'. Like vowel length, consonant length is not very stable; long consonants tend to be shortened in many cases (e.g. the Arabic loan <i>dùkkáán</i> ‘shop’ is often found as <i>dùkáán</i>).</p>
<table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;">
